# go-public (Cursor rule)

The full go-public workflow, phase decision tree, safety rules, and required commands are
maintained once, in the canonical **[AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md)** at the repository root.
Read it before acting — this rule is a thin pointer so the procedure stays identical
across every agent.

Start with:

```bash
scripts/go-public audit --dry-run --report go-public-report.json
```

`scripts/go-public` owns the gates. Dry-run is the default; mutations require `--apply`
or `--apply-history`; remote pushes require `publish --confirm`. Always scan full git
history for secrets and never claim credentials were rotated. See `AGENTS.md` for
everything else.
